# SUPERNOVA MOTORS INC. LITIGATION DOCKET SUMMARY
## Case: Supernova Motors v. Apex Batteries LLC (Cause No. 1:24-cv-01234, U.S. District Court, W.D. TX)
**Filing Date:** March 15, 2024  
**Status:** Pending (Discovery Phase)  
**Plaintiff:** Supernova Motors Inc.  
**Defendant:** Apex Batteries LLC  
**Summary:** Breach of supply contract for lithium-ion cells; alleged defects caused 150-unit recall, $2.5M damages claimed. Settlement discussions ongoing; no reserves disclosed.  
**Key Filings:** 
- Complaint (PDF attached): Alleges warranty breach under UCC § 2-314.  
- Motion to Dismiss (Denied): Defendant claims force majeure (supply chain shortages).  
**Exposure Estimate:** $1.8M (undisclosed in financials).  

## Case: EEOC v. Supernova Motors (Charge No. 450-2024-00567, EEOC Austin District)
**Filing Date:** June 20, 2024  
**Status:** Investigation Open  
**Summary:** Discrimination claim by 12 assembly line workers (gender pay gap); seeks $500K backpay + injunction. No internal grievance resolution.  
**Key Filings:** 
- Charge Letter: Cites Title VII violations.  
- Response (Filed): Denies systemic bias; offers mediation.  
**Exposure Estimate:** $300K (potential class action risk).  

Discrepancy Note: Undisclosed multi-case exposure >$2M; no insurance deductibles detailed—flags litigation reserves gap vs. SEC 10-K benchmarks.